						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Sundararāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription may be assigned to about the 14th century on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a grant as <hi rend="italic">poliūṭṭu</hi> to the deity of the Maṅgaladēvaviṇṇagar temple probably at Kaḍūr Malai maṇḍalam. The details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
